<a id="top"> </a><h1>Tenure-Track Assistant Professorship, LPS, University of California, Irvine</h1>
<p>
The Department of Logic and Philosophy of Science at the University of 
California, Irvine invites applications for a tenure-track Assistant 
Professorship. AOS/AOC: Must include Philosophy of Physics. LPS plans to 
hire at most one new faculty member to begin Fall 2012. Funding for this 
position is contingent on the 2011-12 budget for the University of 
California, Irvine. Applications accepted online beginning Oct 1, 2011. 
<a href="https://recruit.ap.uci.edu/apply#SOCSCI" rel="external">https://recruit.ap.uci.edu/apply#SOCSCI</a>. 
Applications submitted by November 15, 2011 will be considered. 
Application Materials Required:
</p>
<ul class="bullets">
<li>Cover Letter</li>
<li>Curriculum Vitae (most recent)</li>
<li>Research Statement</li>
<li>Writing Sample</li>
<li>3 Letters of Recommendation (minimum)</li>
</ul>
<p>
Optional Materials:
</p>
<ul class="bullets">
<li>Teaching Folio</li>
<li>Additional Writing Sample(s)</li>
</ul>
<p>
The University of California, Irvine is an equal opportunity employer 
committed to excellence through diversity, and strongly encourages 
applications from all qualified applicants, including women and 
minorities. For more information regarding the application process, 
please send your inquiry to: <a href="mailto:lps@uci.edu" rel="email">lps@uci.edu</a>.
</p>
